-- Japan's Orix agrees to buy Hartford Japan unit for $895 million
-- By Taiga Uranaka
-- Mon Apr 28, 2014 02:46AM EDT
-- None



TOKYO, April 28 (Reuters) - Japan's financial company Orix Corp <8591.T> said on Monday it has agreed to buy Hartford Financial Services Group's <HIG.N> Japanese life insurance unit for $895 million in a bid to expand its life insurance business in the world's third-largest economy.

The Orix said the deal is subject to authorities' approval but it aims to complete the acquisition by the end of July.